    h2 How long do coronaviruses persist?
    article.news
        a.news-img(href='#non')
            img(src='http://img17.3lian.com/d/file/201702/24/d32304868431263bad442a9ddac5bfbf.jpg', alt='', width='50', height='50')
        .information-body
            .text
                p
                    | Coronaviruses can remain infectious on inanimate surfaces at room temperature for up to 9 days. At a temperature of 30&deg;C [86&deg;F] or more, the duration of persistence is shorter.
            p.attribution published on 20th Mar 2020
    h2 What is coronavirus?
    article.news
        a.news-img(href='#non')
            img(src='http://img17.3lian.com/d/file/201702/24/d32304868431263bad442a9ddac5bfbf.jpg', alt='', width='50', height='50')
        .information-body
            .text
                 p
                    | COVID-19 actually belongs to a family of coronaviruses (CoV), which include Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS-CoV) and Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS-CoV). According to the World Health Organization, CoVs can afflict
                    | you with something as mild as the common cold or something as deadly as SARS. The virus affecting people now is what&rsquo;s called a novel coronavirus (nCoV) because it&apos;s the first time this particular strain is being seen
                    | in humans.
            p.attribution published on 23th Apr 2020
    h2 Protective measures for Coronavirus
    article.news
        a.news-img(href='#non')
            img(src='http://img17.3lian.com/d/file/201702/24/d32304868431263bad442a9ddac5bfbf.jpg', alt='', width='50', height='50')
        .information-body
            .text
                p
                    | 1) Avoiding close contact with people suffering from acute respiratory infections.
                p
                    | 2) Frequent hand washing, especially after direct contact with sick people or at their residence.
                p
                    | 3) Avoid touching the face and covering the mouth and nose with handkerchief, sleeves or forearms during coughing and sneezing. Dispose of used handkerchief in the nearest waste bin.
                p
                    | 4) If you have a fever, cough and difficulty breathing seek medical help immediately and tell the eventual story of traveling abroad.
                p  5) Sick people should stay home to prevent the spread of the disease.
                p  6) Use health services wisely.
            p.attribution published on 17th Mar 2020
